definition.value: A hydrochloride obtained by combining triethanolamine with one equivalent of hydrogen chloride.
A vanadyl sulfate hydrate containing five water molecules.
A hydrate that is the hexahydrate form of zinc sulfate.
An organic sodium salt consisting of sodium and oxalate ions in a 2:1 ratio.
A hydrate that is the dihydrate form of sodium metavanadate.
An organic sodium salt composed of sodium and nitrilotriacetate ions in a 3:1 ratio.
An iron coordination entity composed from Fe(3+) cations and diphosphate(4-) anions in a 4:3 ratio.
An inorganic sodium salt that has fluorate as the counter-ion.
A sulfonamide consisting of pyridine with a 4-aminobenzenesulfonamido group at the 2-position.
The potassium salt of benazolin. It is used as a post-emergence herbicide for the control of annual weeds in crops.

A branched-chain saturated fatty acid that is tetradecanoic acid in which one of the hydrogens at psoition 10 has been replaced by a methyl group. It is one of a number of methyl-branched fatty acids that have been identified as constituents of sheep perinephric fat.
A carbocyclic fatty acid consisting of octanoic acid, which is terminally substituted by five fused butane-rings ([5]-ladderane). Ladderane fatty acids can be found in anammox bacteria.

An N-substituted putrescine that is thymine in which a hydrogen of the methyl group has been replaced by one of the amino groups of putrescine. It replaces about half of the thymine residues in the DNA of bacetriophage phiW-14.
An octadecenoate in which the double bond is at C-9.
A dicarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of at least one of the carboxy groups of any tartaric acid.
A dicarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of at least one of the carboxy groups of maleic acid.
A dicarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of at least one of the carboxy groups of oxalic acid.
A dicarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of at least one of the carboxy groups of suberic acid.
A dicarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of at least one of the carboxy groups of sebacic acid.
A dicarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of at least one of the carboxy groups of azelaic acid.
An organic anion obtained by deprotonation of at least one of the acidic groups of 3-phosphoglyceric acid.
An N-acylglycinate obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of hippuric acid (N-benzoylglycine) and its derivatives.
An S-acyl-4'-phosphopantetheine obtained by formal condensation of the thiol group of D-pantetheine 4'-phosphate with one of the carboxy groups of malonic acid.
A 3-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-hydroxydecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is the conjugate base of 5-hydroxyhexanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
N-Acetylneuraminic acid reduced across the 2,3-bond with loss of the hydroxy group at C-2 and in which the 9-hydroxy group is substituted by a glutaramido group.
A 2-hydroxy-3-methylpentanoate in which the stereocentres at positions 2 and 3 both have R-configuration.
A branched-chain fatty acid that is 3-methylpentanoic acid carrying a hydroxy substitutent at position 2.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxy-3-methylpentanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An alpha,omega-dicarboxylic acid that is octadecane in which both terminal methyl groups have been replaced by carboxy groups.

A potassium salt resulting from the reaction of equimolar amounts of clofencet and potassium hydroxide. It is used as a chemical hybridisation agent for commercial hybrid seed production. It is not approved for use within the European Union.

A thiazolidine-containing homodetic cyclic peptide that is isolated from human nasal bacteria. Exhibits bactericidal activity against many major pathogens including methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA).

A potassium salt resulting from the reaction of equimolar amounts of karetazan and potassium hydroxide. It is used as a chemical hybridisation agent for commercial hybrid seed production. It is not approved for use within the European Union.
A branched-chain saturated fatty acid that is octadecanoic (stearic) acid carrying a methyl substituent at position 17.
An N-acylhexadecasphingosine-1-phosphocholine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxydecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of oxindoles that is 2-oxindole carrying a carboxymethyl substituent at position 3.
A carboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups of any dicarboxylic acid that contains no carbon-carbon double bonds.
An oxo fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any 3-oxo fatty acid.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups of any oxo dicarboxylic acid.
A metal sulfate with formula BaO4S. Virtually insoluble in water at room temperature, it is mostly used as a component in oil well drilling fluid it occurs naturally as the mineral barite.

A (1->4)-beta-D-glucan consisting of elementary cellulose fibrils or their bundles, whose diameter lies typically in the range of 20-40 nm, but may be as small as 3-10 nm. The fibrils can exceed 1 mum in length.
An N-acylglycine obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of carbamic acid with the amino group of glycine.

An oligosaccharide phosphate consisting of D-myo-inositol having a 6-O-(2-aminoethylphosphono)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-glucosaminyl residue attached at the 6-position.
A PC(18:3/0:0) in which the 1-acyl group is specified as alpha-linolenoyl.
A 3-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-hydroxyoctanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxyoctanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
